# ========================================
# Multi-Tenant Dashboard Configuration
# ========================================
# This dashboard supports two data sources:
# 1. Supabase (PostgreSQL) - for production deployments
# 2. Google Sheets - for clients using spreadsheet-based workflows
#
# Configure ONLY ONE data source per deployment.
# The system will try Supabase first, then Google Sheets, then fall back to mock data.

# ========================================
# Option 1: Supabase Configuration
# ========================================
# Use this for businesses running on Supabase/PostgreSQL
# Example: Spotless Scrubbers production dashboard

# PostgreSQL connection string
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:5432/database

# ========================================
# Option 2: Google Sheets Configuration
# ========================================
# Use this for businesses running on Google Sheets + Lindy automation
# Example: Anna's Cleaning (Figueroa's Maintenance Database)

# Google Spreadsheet ID (from the URL)
# Example: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1PZuxkXpdNzTiSI3hkXrncDPH3T5gpSrg209mMXYEMH4/edit
# The ID is: 1PZuxkXpdNzTiSI3hkXrncDPH3T5gpSrg209mMXYEMH4
SPREADSHEET_ID=your-spreadsheet-id-here

# Google Service Account credentials
# Get these from Google Cloud Console > IAM & Admin > Service Accounts
# 1. Create a service account
# 2. Generate a JSON key
# 3. Share your spreadsheet with the service account email
GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_EMAIL=your-service-account@project-id.iam.gserviceaccount.com
GOOGLE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYour-Private-Key-Here\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"

# ========================================
# Expected Google Sheets Structure
# ========================================
# Your spreadsheet should have these tabs:
#
# 1. "Jobs" sheet with columns:
#    - Title (or Job Title)
#    - Date
#    - Status (scheduled/completed/cancelled)
#    - Customer Name (or Client)
#    - Cleaning Team (comma-separated names)
#    - Booked (TRUE/FALSE)
#    - Paid (TRUE/FALSE)
#    - Price
#    - Phone
#    - Email
#
# 2. "Calls" sheet (optional) with columns:
#    - Phone
#    - Caller Name (or Name)
#    - Date
#    - Duration (in seconds)
#    - Outcome (booked/not_booked/voicemail)
#
# Column names are flexible - the system will try to find them by partial match.
# For example, "Customer Name" will match "Customer", "Name", etc.

# ========================================
# Deployment Examples
# ========================================

# Example 1: Spotless Scrubbers (Supabase)
# Vercel Project: spotless-dashboard
# Environment Variables:
#   DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...
#   (No SPREADSHEET_ID)

# Example 2: Anna's Cleaning (Google Sheets)
# Vercel Project: anna-dashboard
# Environment Variables:
#   SPREADSHEET_ID=1PZuxkXpdNzTiSI3hkXrncDPH3T5gpSrg209mMXYEMH4
#   GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_EMAIL=...
#   GOOGLE_PRIVATE_KEY=...
#   (No DATABASE_URL)

# ========================================
# How to Set Up Google Service Account
# ========================================
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project or select existing
# 3. Enable Google Sheets API
# 4. Go to IAM & Admin > Service Accounts
# 5. Create Service Account
# 6. Click on the service account > Keys > Add Key > Create New Key (JSON)
# 7. Download the JSON file
# 8. Copy the "client_email" to GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_EMAIL
# 9. Copy the "private_key" to GOOGLE_PRIVATE_KEY (keep the \n newlines)
# 10. Share your Google Sheet with the service account email (Viewer access)
